bio.experienceSummary: I am a 35-year-old college educated nanny with tons of experience with children. I have been a caregiver for families for about a decade, taught dance at dance studios and summer camps, and worked as a stage manager/backstage assistant at an acting conservatory for children as well. I am trained to be a birth doula and am pursuing training for postpartum as well. I am fluent in English, Spanish and basic Sign Language. Currently, I'm nannying a toddler, whom has been under my care for the past three years, and now her newborn sister! I'm currently transitioning to NYC. Hope to hear from you!

description.displayText: Elanor was our nanny for 4 years, caring for our son starting at 6 months and continuing through the addition of our twin boys. She is wonderful and hard working, honest and sweet. So deeply caring. So flexible and understanding. Her responsibility grew over the years - she knew the rhythm of our house. She was part of the family. She was incredibly reliable, Always giving lots of advance notice before time off.  She was very careful and cleanly before Covid and obviously with Covid, incredibly careful. She rarely got the common illnesses over the course of the years. We all miss Elanor and wish her all the best.

bio.experienceSummary: I love children and have cared for kids ranging in ages from 3 months to 13 years of age. I love hiking and playing around with kids and love their enthusiasm and imagination. I'm a great multi-tasker and love to clean up whenever I can and wouldn't mind helping with cleaning tasks around the house. I've worked as a housekeeper and as a babysitter in the past and have loved both jobs dearly. Along with this, I also love to cook healthy meals and stay active and would love to cook, play and learn with your little one.

Hi there! I'm a warm and patient 24-year-old artist and textile-maker living in Brooklyn. I graduated cum laude from NYU two years ago where I studied mental health with a focus on children. I am passionate about early childhood, and in another year or two, I plan to go back to school for my masters in art therapy. I am looking to nanny part-time so I can pursue my artistic and educational goals simultaneously!

I adore children and have been babysitting since an early age. In addition, I have four years of experience working with infants aged 3 months- children aged 12+ in classroom, daycare, summer camp, and home settings. I've spent the past 2 years nannying and I genuinely look forward to going to work every day. I've been described by my previous nanny family as "sweet, kind, mature, and an incredible addition to our team."

I am fully vaccinated and boosted, CPR and First Aid certified, and I have received my flu shot. I can't wait to meet you! :)

description.originalText: Rosalind—Lindy—was kind, intuitive, and reliable. Our son was delighted on the mornings when she’d arrive, brimming with ideas of how to spend their day together. It gave us great peace of mind to know that our child was with someone as capable as she was thoughtful.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello! My name is Madison and right now I am living one of my dreams of being a nanny in NYC working for a lovely family with 3 kids. From a young age, I've always had a passion for children.
I graduated from the University of Arizona with a Bachelors in Communication, and I also got my Masters degree in Organizational Leadership and Change. After college, I was working in higher education and recently hopped out to nanny.
Throughout college I was a nanny full time to 2 wonderful families. I also worked for other families on the side as needed. After college I decided to hop into the corporate world/ higher education, but I've learned working with children is what makes me happy.
Currently I am looking to assist with date nights or weekend care.
I can provide multiple references if need be.
I am CPR and Babysitter certified, and willing to go through additional certifications to make you feel comfortable.
I look forward to hearing from you!

description.displayText: Madison was my sons nanny from the time he was about 9 months- 18 months. We adored her and our son did too. She has great communication, is a natural with children and is very responsible. We missed her greatly when our childcare situation changed but she would still offer to help us out whenever we needed a sitter. Any family who has Madison looking after their children is very lucky to have her!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hey, I'm Cristina. I've been working with kids for over 10 years, wearing different hats such as mentor, educator, and friend - from newborns to teenagers. I believe kids are infinitely capable. I want youth to thrive and support them to grow emotionally, gain confidence, and tap into their creativity.

I'm all about curiosity and learning, promoting hands-on exploration -- think wonder, experiments, outdoor games, and cultural outings.

Building trust with both kids and their families is key for me. It's about creating a safe space and openly communicating to create the best environment for all.

I'm available for weekend and holiday travel nannying, and have experience in both the U. S. and abroad. If this sounds like it aligns with your needs, let's chat to see if we'd be a good fit! I look forward to hearing from you!

Starting rate is $35/hour or $450/day for travel.

I am also a movement based educator (Pilates) and have experience in mindfulness.

description.displayText: An amazing sweetheart.  She is so reliable and kind.  She made herself available last minute and provided me with the best childcare I've received in a while.  She took my son to the park they played and a waterfall and she sent me lots of amazing pics.  My son seemed very comfortable and happy and I would hire her over and over again thank you so much Christina.

bio.experienceSummary: My name is Alli, and I have extensive experience being a part-time nanny on and off since I moved to NYC almost 10 years ago! I have a full-time job, but work in the non-profit/education field so have always looked to nannying for supplemental income whenever I need some spending money. I am originally from California and have a huge family (most of whom are still in CA), so I miss being around kids often and view nannying as a win win for both me and the families I sit for! I have experience with children ranging from 4 weeks old to 16 years old. I enjoy baking, cooking, working out, reading, and exploring new places. I can't wait to meet your family!

I am the oldest of 5 children, with a 12-year gap between myself and the youngest which is where my love for kids stems from and my experience with childcare. I'm a very happy person, as well as intuitive, responsible, detail-oriented, and loving. I love to travel, experience new things, meet new people, and spend time with my family. I'd love to chat more about how I can fit your family's needs! I'm looking for a live-in position in the city and am willing to travel as much as you need.

Hello, my name is Kayla. I've been working in my field for about 10 years. I started very young because I knew exactly what I wanted to do at a young age. I was able to be a part of many families and gained so much experience, patience, and humbling lessons working with children of all ages starting at newborn. I currently have families I work with occasionally for date nights etc. I have worked in house cleaning and done solo jobs in homes. I am currently an assistant, I would say I have amazing management skills, communication skills, organizational skills etc. I am willing to learn anything new; I am a hands-on learner. When it comes to food I will base it off the parents open to learning any recipes, if not we free style! I am grateful for any opportunity if you have any questions, please feel free to contact me!
**My availability is open for conversation **

description.originalText: She’s great taking care of my elderly father while I’m at work. She cleaned my house also, took my dad on walks. Also to his appointments when I’m unable to. She also have a great outgoing personality.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! I am a 30-year-old who works fulltime in finance. I have my MBA and moved to the city about 6 months ago. Seeking part-time work as a nanny to help repay student loans. I am the oldest of 7 children and grew up babysitting both my younger siblings and other families. I am free weekends during the day + date nights. Not a big fan of screen time so will try my best to keep the kids engaged while I am with them. Happy to help with cooking + tidying while tending to the kids.

Executive Nanny.
Over 19 years of paid experience in nanny services
Certified Newborn Care Specialist
 Languages spoken: English, Spanish, Portuguese
 CPR/AED training completed (infant/child/adult)
 Professional organizer
Travel Nanny (international and domestic)
 Comfortable with pets

continuing undergraduate studies in psychology (online)

description.displayText: I recently used Betania's services as a (short-term) live-in nanny and housekeeper, and I highly recommend her! I had to travel for about a week for work, and Betania took special care of my 2-year old and 6-year-old children. She also helped out my elderly mom around the house. Everything went smoothly! My kids loved her, and the house was well-maintained! Very responsible and sweet! I would definitely use her again! Recommended!
